column5: Looking for the latest on Minaki going up the 17th through the 26th of July whats been going on. How is the water level.Thanks for any help.

Despite what you might be hearing, the water level is only about 1 foot below normal.....people just think it is really low because it's been really high for the last several years......if you've never been there it will appear normal. Sorry, no fishing updates from me as I got back two weeks ago......you should miss the mayfly hatch though as it was early this year.
